{
  "stem": "2067.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because of the dire economic situation in Germany, imports had been curtailed, and my father's business almost stopped.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "His business relationships and friends in Holland and Belgium informed him that Spain had become one of the largest importers of eggs in Western Europe.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they suggested that he make a business trip to Spain to find out whether there was any chance to work together in Spain.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Barcelona they recommended as the commercial city where it would be the best place to-- to go to.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Since my father didn't speak French, but I did, and I had my spring vacation in college, he said to me to come along to be--",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To Spain.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To accompanying him to Spain.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nope.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Neither one of us spoke one word of Spanish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went first to Holland, to Belgium, spoke to our friends, and we continued to Spain.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This is then March 1933.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Shortly after-- after-- a few weeks after our arrival, a letter came from my brother from Frankfurt-- he had stayed behind with my mother-- to informing us that one of the first anti-Jewish decrees of the new Nazi regime was to ban all Jews from college and also Jewish professors.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In other words, my medical career in Germany had ended.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So did my brother's, who had also started a medical career in Holland-- in Germany.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Right then and there, I-- my father and I decided, we are not going back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had, of course, seen the growing Nazi danger in Germany by the constant marches of the brown shirts through the streets of Frankfurt, and clashes between the Nazis and the Socialists and especially the Communists.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I worried about the political condition in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
